juniOspfMIB.name: juniOspfMIB

revisions.description: Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Added juniOspfVpnRouteTag, juniOspfDomainId, juniOspfAreaTeCapable and juniOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex objects.
Key revisions include: o Corrected description for juniOspfProcessId. o Added juniOspfNetworkRangeTable. o Added juniOspfOperState.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniOspfMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@Juniper.net
juniOspfMIB.description: The OSPF Protocol MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

juniOspfProcessId.name: juniOspfProcessId
juniOspfProcessId.description: An identifier having special semantics when set. When this object's value is zero, OSPF is disabled and cannot be configured. Setting this object to a nonzero value enables OSPF operation and permits further OSPF configuration to be performed. Once set to a nonzero value, this object cannot be modified.

juniOspfMaxPathSplits.name: juniOspfMaxPathSplits
juniOspfMaxPathSplits.description: The maximum number of equal-cost routes that will be maintained by the OSPF protocol. A change in this value will be taken into account at the next shortest-path-first recalculation.

juniOspfSpfHoldInterval.name: juniOspfSpfHoldInterval
juniOspfSpfHoldInterval.description: The minimum amount of time that must elapse between shortest-path-first recalculations. Reducing this value can cause an immediate SPF recalulation if the new value is less than the current value of juniOspfSpfHoldTimeRemaining and other SPF-inducing protocol events have occurred.

juniOspfRefBw.name: juniOspfRefBw
juniOspfRefBw.description: The reference bandwith, in bits per second. This object is used when OSPF automatic interface cost calculation is used.

juniOspfAutoVlink.name: juniOspfAutoVlink
juniOspfAutoVlink.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have virtual links automatically configured.

juniOspfExtDistance.name: juniOspfExtDistance
juniOspfExtDistance.description: Default distance for external type 5 and type 7 routes.

juniOspfDDPktsRcv.description: Number of database description packets received.

juniOspfLsrPktsRcv.name: juniOspfLsrPktsRcv
juniOspfLsrPktsRcv.description: Number of link state request packets received.

juniOspfLsAckPktsRcv.name: juniOspfLsAckPktsRcv
juniOspfLsAckPktsRcv.description: Number of link state ACK packets received.

juniOspfDDPktsSent.description: Number of database description packets sent.

juniOspfLsAckPktsSent.name: juniOspfLsAckPktsSent
juniOspfLsAckPktsSent.description: Number of link state ACK packets sent.

juniOspfCsumErrPkts.name: juniOspfCsumErrPkts
juniOspfCsumErrPkts.description: Number of packets received with a checksum error.

juniOspfAllocFailDbRequest.description: Number of database request allocation failures.

juniOspfAllocFailAck.name: juniOspfAllocFailAck
juniOspfAllocFailAck.description: Number of LS ACK allocation failures.

juniOspfAllocFailPkt.name: juniOspfAllocFailPkt
juniOspfAllocFailPkt.description: Number of OSPF general packet allocation failures.

juniOspfOperState.name: juniOspfOperState
juniOspfOperState.description: A flag to note whether this router is operational.

juniOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex.name: juniOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex
juniOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex.description: Configure the stable router interface id to designate it as TE capable.

juniOspfAreaTable.name: juniOspfAreaTable
juniOspfAreaTable.description: The Juniper OSPF area table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of areas.

juniOspfAreaEntry.name: juniOspfAreaEntry
juniOspfAreaEntry.description: The OSPF area entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one area.

juniOspfAreaTeCapable.name: juniOspfAreaTeCapable
juniOspfAreaTeCapable.description: Configure the specified area TE capable to flood the TE information.

juniOspfIfTable.name: juniOspfIfTable
juniOspfIfTable.description: The Juniper OSPF interface table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of interfaces.

juniOspfIfEntry.description: The OSPF interface entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one interface.

juniOspfIfCost.name: juniOspfIfCost
juniOspfIfCost.description: The cost value for this interface.

juniOspfIfMask.name: juniOspfIfMask
juniOspfIfMask.description: The mask used to derive the network range of this interface.

juniOspfIfPassiveFlag.name: juniOspfIfPassiveFlag
juniOspfIfPassiveFlag.description: Flag to indicate whether routing updates should be suppressed on this interface. To actively perform routing updates, set this object to disabled(0).

juniOspfIfNbrCount.name: juniOspfIfNbrCount
juniOspfIfNbrCount.description: Number of OSPF neighbors from this interface.

juniOspfIfAdjNbrCount.name: juniOspfIfAdjNbrCount
juniOspfIfAdjNbrCount.description: Number of OSPF adjacent neighbors from this interface.

juniOspfIfMd5AuthKey.name: juniOspfIfMd5AuthKey
juniOspfIfMd5AuthKey.description: The MD5 authentication key. When setting this object, the juniOspfIfMd5AuthKeyId must be specified on the same PDU. For simple text authentication type, use ospfIfAuthKey. Setting this object will have the side effect of adding or updating the correspondent entry in juniOspfMd5IntfKeyTable. If key given has less than 16 octets, such value will be appended with zeros to complete 16 octets. The zeros will appended to the right of the given key. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

juniOspfIfMd5AuthKeyId.name: juniOspfIfMd5AuthKeyId
juniOspfIfMd5AuthKeyId.description: The MD5 authentication key ID. When setting this object, juniOspfIfMd5AuthKey must be specified on the same PDU.

juniOspfVirtIfTable.name: juniOspfVirtIfTable
juniOspfVirtIfTable.description: The Juniper OSPF virtual interface table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of virtual interfaces.

juniOspfVirtIfEntry.name: juniOspfVirtIfEntry
juniOspfVirtIfEntry.description: The OSPF virtual interface entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one virtual interface.

juniOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKey.name: juniOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKey
juniOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKey.description: The MD5 authentication key. When setting this object, the juniOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKeyId must be specified on the same PDU. For simple text authentication type, use ospfVirtIfAuthKey. Setting this object will have the side effect of adding or updating the correspondent entry in juniOspfMd5IntfKeyTable. If key given has less than 16 octets, such value will be appended with zeros to complete 16 octets. The zeros will appended to the right of the given key. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

juniOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKeyId.name: juniOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKeyId
juniOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKeyId.description: The MD5 authentication key id. When setting this object, juniOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKey must be specified on the same psu.

juniOspfNbrDR.name: juniOspfNbrDR
juniOspfNbrDR.description: The neighbor's idea of designated router.

juniOspfNbrBDR.name: juniOspfNbrBDR
juniOspfNbrBDR.description: The neighbor's idea of backup designated router.

juniOspfSummImportTable.name: juniOspfSummImportTable
juniOspfSummImportTable.description: The Juniper OSPF summary import table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of network aggregation into the OSPF autonomous system. With this table, the load of advertising many external routes can be reduced by specifying a range which includes some or all of the external routes.

juniOspfSummImportEntry.name: juniOspfSummImportEntry
juniOspfSummImportEntry.description: The OSPF summary import entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one summary report.

juniOspfSummAggNet.name: juniOspfSummAggNet
juniOspfSummAggNet.description: The summary address for a range of addresses.

juniOspfSummAggMask.name: juniOspfSummAggMask
juniOspfSummAggMask.description: The subnet mask used for the summary route.

juniOspfSummAdminStat.name: juniOspfSummAdminStat
juniOspfSummAdminStat.description: The admin status of this summary aggregation.

juniOspfSummRowStatus.name: juniOspfSummRowStatus
juniOspfSummRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry.

juniOspfMd5IntfEntry.description: The OSPF interface MD5 key entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one MD5 authentication's interface.

juniOspfMd5IntfKeyId.name: juniOspfMd5IntfKeyId
juniOspfMd5IntfKeyId.description: The OSPF interface this key belongs to.

juniOspfMd5IntfKeyActive.name: juniOspfMd5IntfKeyActive
juniOspfMd5IntfKeyActive.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have this key active.

juniOspfMd5IntfAuthKey.name: juniOspfMd5IntfAuthKey
juniOspfMd5IntfAuthKey.description: The MD5 authentication key. If key given has less than 16 octets, such value will be appended with zeros to complete 16 octets. The zeros will appended to the right of the given key. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

juniOspfMd5IntfRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry.

juniOspfMd5VirtIntfEntry.description: The OSPF Interface MD5 Key entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one MD5 authentication's interface.

juniOspfMd5VirtIntfAreaId.description: The OSPF area ID this key belongs to.

juniOspfMd5VirtIntfNeighbor.description: The OSPF neightbor this key belongs to.

juniOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyId.description: The OSPF virtual interface this key belongs to.

juniOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyActive.name: juniOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyActive
juniOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyActive.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have this key active.

juniOspfMd5VirtIntfAuthKey.description: The MD5 authentication key. If key given has less than 16 octets, such value will be appended with zeros to complete 16 octets. The zeros will appended to the right of the given key. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

juniOspfMd5VirtIntfRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry.

juniOspfNetworkRangeTable.name: juniOspfNetworkRangeTable
juniOspfNetworkRangeTable.description: The Juniper OSPF network range table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of network ranges, encompassing one or multiple OSPF interfaces.

juniOspfNetworkRangeEntry.description: The Juniper OSPF network range entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one OSPF network range.

juniOspfNetRangeMask.description: The subnet mask used for the network range. Unlike the mask used under the command line interface (CLI), this object is set in the non-inversed format (i.e. not a wild-card mask).

juniOspfNetRangeRowStatus.name: juniOspfNetRangeRowStatus

juniOspfIfBfdMinRxInterval.name: juniOspfIfBfdMinRxInterval
